<p>*Please check with RecSports for more information for job descriptions</p>
<p>To apply please have a resume and cover letter complete and submit them in the application questionair.&nbsp; You can start the application <a href="https://byui.qualtrics.com/SE/?SID=SV_5BVoPQHkqDIetTK" target="_blank">here</a>.&nbsp; Please complete it, there is not a save option so once you start you need to finish.</p>
<p>Around second block each semester RecSports starts the application process for the following semester's positions.&nbsp; First we start with the application for Area Director then Directors, Coordinators, and then Managers.&nbsp; By tradition we like to move students up through the process enabling them to gain more experience and help them be better prepared for the paid positions.</p>
<p>Typically new students will start off in a volunteer position making their way to a paid manager or coordinator position.&nbsp; Those paid positions are hourly rates with a hours per week limitation.&nbsp; The Area Director and some Director positions are tuition based positions, meaning you get free tuition. Note: less than half of all managers or coordinators are paid.</p>
